<br>
I'm around 784 AC right now (while wielding a shield) with my self buffs of Daring and Guard, which I didn't think was too bad, but I've heard it said once that &quot;good&quot; AC for a paladin/warrior/SK means it's higher than your ATK, which isn't the case with me.  I also seem to be finding myself grouped with other tanks of similar level that have 800+ AC when they aren't buffed.<br>
<br>
The biggest trouble is that armor upgrades are no where in sight for me.  I don't have any Ro armor yet, but all of its pieces are the same AC as the pieces I'm already wearing -- and sometimes less.  (I'm in a mixture of things: lightcrawler, enameled black BP, fine plate, skull-sharped barbute.)  What I see ahead of me is Acrylia, Deepwater, and Dwarven Plate, all of which are *way* out of my price range.  (A single bracer or pair of boots would clean out my bank.)<br>
<br>
Should I be really scrimping and saving to upgrade my armor?  Is there some armor I'm missing that is a nice medium between between Ro-type armor and the higher crafted armor that I can quest/hunt for, or reasonably purchase?  I'd like to save for some sort of Haste item, too, but I don't know if I need to get better armor first.<br>
<br>
At any rate, I'm not yet so bad that a group asks if I'll let someone else tank, but maybe they fear the wrath of a gnome. /chuckle <p> <div align="center"><center><img src="http://www.members.shaw.ca/vae/sigv2-5.jpg"><BR><a href="http://www.byteoart.com/ledenyetz/">Ledenyetz Troupe</a></div></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udaliondveldrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalion DVeldrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I put the inky in kinky</span><br>  Posts: 540<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/02 4:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.animationlibrary.com/Animation11/Animals/Rabbits/Realistic_bunny_2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What kind of armor did you have?</span><hr size=1> I believe at this season, it would be best to quest your Ro armor, or perhaps purchase some crustacean shell armor. I basically got my darkforge armor at about 35, then went on to fill certain spots with crustacean shell armor, bypassed Shadowknight Fear planar and went straight for PoG/Thurgadin armor.<br>
<br>
Thats usually how most hybrids do it. Ro armor, some in between like crusty, planar armor then Velious armors. Crustacean shell armor may not have the best ac, but the stam more than makes up for it. I also do not believe it is terribly expensive compared to Acrylia/kunark armors (depending on the piece anywhere from 200-500?).<br>
<br>
As for haste, that should be your first priority. More haste means you kill each mob faster. The faster they die, the less hits you take. I'd suggest saving up for a haste item first (e.g. Silver chitin handwraps, Fbss etc) then further along the line fill your lesser spots with crustacean shelled armor.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp. <p><center><a href=http://www.ebonstorm.com/index><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/teneel/Dalion.jpg></a><br><b> Harbinger of Vengeance</b><br><i> ~* He who follows his heart will find that it will bleed *~</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1238<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/02 7:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The quested sol-ro temple armor ..</span><hr size=1> .. will last you well in to your 50's.  I recall warriors that wore mostly crafted at 60 and didn't bother to upgrade until they were doing raids.  In general, if you're wanting to make your character stronger, there is nothing you can do that is better than leveling up.  Leveling will not only give you access to better gear, it will make it easier to acquire, too.<br>
<br>
If you see a good deal on an upgrade as you level up, go ahead and buy it.  Same thing with a fun quest or other item desire.  For instance, collecting a full suit of a particularly snazzy armor set can be a lot of fun.  It is a game to play for fun after all (and endless xp grinding can feel like work).<br>
<br>
The bazaar and recent increased trading pace on FV has put a lot of focus on buying up armor, too (eg. your bogglement on how to save up to buy armor).  Don't forget that the best armor always comes from MOB drops and the easiest way by far to get those is to go out and hunt them down.  It's fun, it's free, and you get xp doing it, too.<br>
<br>
